     1→---
     2→name: CC MCP Integration
     3→description: Configure and integrate MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers for external data access. Use when connecting to GitHub, databases, Slack, or custom APIs.
     4→version: 1.0.0
     5→tags: [claude-code, cc, mcp, integration, protocols, external-data]
     6→---
     7→
     8→# CC MCP Integration
     9→
    10→## Quick Start
    11→
    12→MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers connect Claude Code to external systems and APIs. They provide tools for accessing real-time data like GitHub repositories, databases, Slack workspaces, or custom services.
    13→
    14→### Minimal MCP Configuration
    15→```json
    16→{
    17→  "mcpServers": {
    18→    "github": {
    19→      "command": "npx",
    20→      "args": ["-y", "github-mcp"]
    21→    }
    22→  }
    23→}
    24→```
    25→
    26→### File Location
    27→Add MCP servers to `~/.claude/settings.json` under `mcpServers` object.
    28→
    29→### Configuration Fields
    30→
    31→| Field | Required | Purpose |
    32→|-------|----------|---------|
    33→| `command` | Yes | Executable to run (npx, python, node, etc) |
    34→| `args` | No | Arguments to pass to command |
    35→| `env` | No | Environment variables for server |
    36→
    37→## Core Concepts
    38→
    39→### What is MCP?
    40→
    41→MCP (Model Context Protocol) is a standardized interface that lets Claude:
    42→1. Discover what tools a server provides
    43→2. Call remote tools through the server
    44→3. Access real-time external data
    45→
    46→**Examples:**
    47→- GitHub MCP: access repos, PRs, issues in real-time
    48→- Slack MCP: read channels, messages, user info
    49→- Database MCP: query databases, run migrations
    50→- Custom MCP: integrate your own APIs
    51→
    52→### MCP vs Skills vs Subagents
    53→
    54→| Aspect | MCP Server | Skill | Subagent |
    55→|--------|-----------|-------|----------|
    56→| **Access** | External data | Local knowledge | Specialized AI |
    57→| **Updates** | Real-time | Static (session) | Real-time reasoning |
    58→| **Example** | "Get latest GitHub issues" | "How to create a PR" | "Security auditor" |
    59→| **When** | Current data needed | Reference knowledge | Decision-making |
    60→
    61→## Common MCP Servers
    62→
    63→### GitHub MCP
    64→Real-time access to GitHub repositories, PRs, issues, commits.
    65→
    66→**Setup:**
    67→```json
    68→{
    69→  "mcpServers": {
    70→    "github": {
    71→      "command": "npx",
    72→      "args": ["-y", "github-mcp"],
    73→      "env": {
    74→        "GITHUB_TOKEN": "your-token-here"
    75→      }
    76→    }
    77→  }
    78→}
    79→```
    80→
    81→**Provides Tools:**
    82→- List repositories
    83→- Get repository details
    84→- List pull requests
    85→- Get PR details and reviews
    86→- List issues
    87→- Create/update issues
    88→- Comment on PRs/issues
    89→
    90→**Example Usage:**
    91→```
    92→"Get all open PRs in my repo"
    93→→ GitHub MCP provides PR data
    94→```
    95→
    96→### Slack MCP
    97→Access Slack channels, messages, users, and workspace data.
    98→
    99→**Setup:**
   100→```json
   101→{
   102→  "mcpServers": {
   103→    "slack": {
   104→      "command": "npx",
   105→      "args": ["-y", "slack-mcp"],
   106→      "env": {
   107→        "SLACK_BOT_TOKEN": "xoxb-your-token",
   108→        "SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET": "your-signing-secret"
   109→      }
   110→    }
   111→  }
   112→}
   113→```
   114→
   115→**Provides Tools:**
   116→- List channels
   117→- Get channel history
   118→- Send messages
   119→- Search messages
   120→- Get user profiles
   121→- List users
   122→
   123→**Example Usage:**
   124→```
   125→"Summarize #engineering channel for today"
   126→→ Slack MCP fetches messages and provides context
   127→```
   128→
   129→### PostgreSQL MCP
   130→Query PostgreSQL databases directly.
   131→
   132→**Setup:**
   133→```json
   134→{
   135→  "mcpServers": {
   136→    "postgres": {
   137→      "command": "npx",
   138→      "args": ["-y", "postgres-mcp"],
   139→      "env": {
   140→        "DATABASE_URL": "postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/mydb"
   141→      }
   142→    }
   143→  }
   144→}
   145→```
   146→
   147→**Provides Tools:**
   148→- Query database (SELECT)
   149→- Execute migrations
   150→- Get schema information
   151→- List tables
   152→
   153→**Example Usage:**
   154→```
   155→"What are the top 10 users by activity?"
   156→→ PostgreSQL MCP queries the database
   157→```
   158→
   159→### Custom REST API MCP
   160→Build your own MCP for custom APIs.
   161→
   162→**Example Structure:**
   163→```javascript
   164→// Simple custom MCP server
   165→const { Server } = require("@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio");
   166→
   167→const server = new Server({
   168→  name: "my-api",
   169→  version: "1.0.0"
   170→});
   171→
   172→server.setRequestHandler(async (request) => {
   173→  if (request.method === "tools/list") {
   174→    return {
   175→      tools: [
   176→        {
   177→          name: "get_user",
   178→          description: "Get user by ID",
   179→          inputSchema: {
   180→            type: "object",
   181→            properties: {
   182→              id: { type: "string" }
   183→            }
   184→          }
   185→        }
   186→      ]
   187→    };
   188→  }
   189→});
   190→```
   191→
   192→## Patterns
   193→
   194→### Pattern 1: Data Aggregation
   195→```json
   196→{
   197→  "mcpServers": {
   198→    "github": {
   199→      "command": "npx",
   200→      "args": ["-y", "github-mcp"],
   201→      "env": {"GITHUB_TOKEN": "${GITHUB_TOKEN}"}
   202→    },
   203→    "slack": {
   204→      "command": "npx",
   205→      "args": ["-y", "slack-mcp"],
   206→      "env": {"SLACK_BOT_TOKEN": "${SLACK_BOT_TOKEN}"}
   207→    }
   208→  }
   209→}
   210→```
   211→
   212→**Use Case:** Access GitHub and Slack together
   213→- Get PRs from GitHub
   214→- Post PR summaries to Slack channel
   215→
   216→### Pattern 2: Real-Time Decision Making
   217→```json
   218→{
   219→  "mcpServers": {
   220→    "postgres": {
   221→      "command": "npx",
   222→      "args": ["-y", "postgres-mcp"],
   223→      "env": {"DATABASE_URL": "${DATABASE_URL}"}
   224→    }
   225→  }
   226→}
   227→```
   228→
   229→**Use Case:** Query database before making recommendations
   230→- Check current database state
   231→- Analyze patterns
   232→- Make informed decisions
   233→
   234→### Pattern 3: Development Context
   235→```json
   236→{
   237→  "mcpServers": {
   238→    "github": {
   239→      "command": "npx",
   240→      "args": ["-y", "github-mcp"],
   241→      "env": {"GITHUB_TOKEN": "${GITHUB_TOKEN}"}
   242→    }
   243→  }
   244→}
   245→```
   246→
   247→**Use Case:** Understand codebase changes
   248→- Check recent commits
   249→- Review open PRs
   250→- Understand issue context
   251→
   252→## Best Practices
   253→
   254→### DO: Use Environment Variables for Secrets
   255→```json
   256→// Good - uses env variables
   257→{
   258→  "env": {
   259→    "GITHUB_TOKEN": "${GITHUB_TOKEN}",
   260→    "API_KEY": "${API_KEY}"
   261→  }
   262→}
   263→
   264→// Bad - secrets in config
   265→{
   266→  "env": {
   267→    "GITHUB_TOKEN": "ghp_1234567890abcdef"
   268→  }
   269→}
   270→```
   271→
   272→### DO: Set Environment Variables Securely
   273→```bash
   274→# Export before running Claude Code
   275→export GITHUB_TOKEN="ghp_your_token_here"
   276→export SLACK_BOT_TOKEN="xoxb_your_token_here"
   277→
   278→# Or set in ~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc
   279→echo 'export GITHUB_TOKEN="..."' >> ~/.zshrc
   280→```
   281→
   282→### DO: Test MCP Connection
   283→```bash
   284→# Test if MCP server starts correctly
   285→npx -y github-mcp
   286→# Should output: {"jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 1, "method": "initialize", ...}
